review_title: Great value, but wears out in high friction areas
reviews: I'm a husky guy who's thighs rub when I'm out and about, so I prefer a longer inseam on my briefs. These have a good length, and also good value. That said, after about half a year some of mine have started to wear out. I've also noticed that with the cotton, after a day's wear they are less form fitting and almost like boxers. They're alright for the money, but for a little more bang for your buck try out Fruit of the Loom's "Mens 3-Pack Breathable Long Leg Boxer Brief Boxer Briefs." The 3 pack with two blacks and a light grey have resolved these issues for me.
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Mens Coolzone Boxer Briefs Underwear

review_title: Unexpectedly low rise waist: exposure plus uncomfortable
reviews:
Their unexpectedly low rise waist, maybe 3/4 inch less than I am used to with Fruit of the Loom, gives rise to "plumbers butt", but also it is uncomfortable.

I much preferred the previous Fruit of the Loom style where the waist band was 3/4 inch higher and did not rub my tail bone.

Otherwise, good quality. But sadly I'll now be looking for a different brand with a more comfortable fit.
